sentences.sContent: She has put into the small, unwise head of the chipmunk the untutored fear of poisons.
sentences.sContent_eng: She has put into the small, unwise head of the chipmunk the untutored fear of poisons.
sentences.sCn: 花栗鼠愚蠢的小脑袋里却有天生的对于毒药的恐惧。

sentences.sContent: The weasel population also increased, following the growth of the chipmunk population.
sentences.sContent_eng: The weasel population also increased, following the growth of the chipmunk population.
sentences.sCn: 黄鼠狼群也随着金花鼠数目的增加增长了。

sentences.sContent: When a squirrel or a rabbit or a chipmunk freezes, it can remain almost entirely motionless for minutes at a time.
sentences.sContent_eng: When a squirrel or a rabbit or a chipmunk freezes, it can remain almost entirely motionless for minutes at a time.
sentences.sCn: 当一只松鼠，兔子或花栗鼠冻结时，它可以一次保持完全静止不动达数分钟之久。

trans.tranOther: a small American animal similar to a  squirrel  with black lines on its fur
